MinstrelS‚ TrouveurS, and Joculators, at once poetS, actorS, buffoonS, and beggars, were paid, courted, and rewarded by him : and the market-places resounded with the venal strains recounting the Bishop's fame and praise.—-Had these rbymes alone sur- vived‚ how different would have been the tale. ,
